goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This tells us how frequently flights are delayed and by how much time.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?
goals.rationale: This tells us how far most flights travel and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight delays and distances?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of delay vs distance
goals.rationale: This helps us understand if there is a correlation between flight delays and distances.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight durations?
goals.rationale: This tells us how long most flights take and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight distances and durations?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of distance vs time
goals.rationale: This helps us understand if there is a correlation between flight distances and durations.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    ax.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean = {data['delay'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median = {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['distance'])
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='green', label='Median distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between flight delays and distances?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['time'] = data['time'].dt.hour + data['time'].dt.minute/60
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['time'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    ax.axvline(data['time'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median = {:.2f}'.format(data['time'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight durations?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
